    "body": "On AMD/ROCm systems, especially with RDNA-based GPUs (where only the Triton backend is supported), it's currently necessary to manually set `FLASH_ATTENTION_TRITON_AMD_ENABLE=TRUE`. This change implements a fallback that automatically switches to the Triton backend if it's a HIP system and the main C++ extension (`flash_attn_2_cuda`) is not available. Tested on gfx1201.",
